15:03.847 --> 15:05.776
A duel it is.

15:05.845 --> 15:07.344
To the death.

15:07.411 --> 15:08.709
Artistically speaking.

15:11.076 --> 15:12.340
[BLOWING]

15:12.409 --> 15:14.106
Warm my fingers, please, Garfield.

15:14.173 --> 15:15.437
Do you have one of those glass things

15:15.505 --> 15:16.837
you put on your finger?

15:16.904 --> 15:18.435
The duel was under your initiation.

15:18.505 --> 15:19.736
- You begin.
- Fine.

15:19.804 --> 15:22.234
Garfield, give us a C, please.

15:23.834 --> 15:25.200
[HUMS NOTE]

15:25.266 --> 15:27.196
- [BOTH STRUMMING]
- Ooh, that's off.

15:27.266 --> 15:28.664
- That's off, isn't it?
- Yes.

15:28.732 --> 15:31.029
We'll just try that again.

15:31.098 --> 15:32.429
[STRUMMING TUNE]

15:32.496 --> 15:33.594
It's probably easier if I tune to you.

15:33.664 --> 15:34.595
Fine.

15:34.661 --> 15:37.591
[BOTH STRUMMING]

15:37.661 --> 15:39.258
[HUMMING]

15:39.326 --> 15:41.523
- Does that sound okay?
- [HUMMING]

15:41.592 --> 15:43.024
- What note is that?
- I don't know.

15:43.091 --> 15:44.854
Do you know, "Oh, He's My Savior,

15:44.922 --> 15:46.853
- Let Him Come Amongst Us"?
- Do you have a tuning fork?

15:46.922 --> 15:48.852
Do you know, "Oh, Christ, Here He Is"?

15:48.920 --> 15:50.752
Do you know "Camptown Races"?

15:50.819 --> 15:52.982
Do you know, "Oh, Gay Are
The Days For He Is The One"?

15:53.052 --> 15:54.983
Do you know, "Champagne
Charlie Was His Name"?

15:55.049 --> 15:56.615
How does that go?

15:56.683 --> 15:58.613
- Is that...
- ♪ Champagne Charlie ♪

15:58.680 --> 16:00.378
- [BOTH SINGING]
- Are you alone?

16:02.611 --> 16:04.111
Does it look like I'm alone?

16:04.179 --> 16:05.611
Yes.

16:05.678 --> 16:07.376
There are two other men in this room.

16:07.443 --> 16:08.875
Yes, but I always
[Bleep] in front of them.

16:08.942 --> 16:10.373
It's true.

16:10.442 --> 16:13.206
I've been very bad, Padre.

16:13.274 --> 16:16.203
You may need to spank me.

16:16.270 --> 16:18.102
- Frederick.
- Mmm?

16:18.170 --> 16:20.534
I will never, ever make love to you.

16:20.602 --> 16:22.531
Ever.

16:22.601 --> 16:25.532
[SOBBING]

16:25.598 --> 16:28.362
We'll continue this later, sir.

16:28.432 --> 16:30.997
Don't get on my bad side, Peepers.

16:31.063 --> 16:32.995
I intend to be here

16:33.062 --> 16:34.991
for a very long time.

16:35.060 --> 16:37.224
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:37.293 --> 16:38.826
[GAVEL BANGING]

16:38.893 --> 16:40.823
Speaking on behalf of women's suffrage,

16:40.890 --> 16:42.820
Beatrice and Lillian Bellacourt.

16:42.890 --> 16:47.218
It's actually pronounced
Lillian and Beatrice Bellacourt.

16:47.286 --> 16:50.051
Ladies, you have the floor.

16:50.120 --> 16:53.051
Why should women get the right to vote?

16:53.116 --> 16:57.346
Why should women get the right to vote?

16:59.780 --> 17:02.210
On the one hand, voting could lead

17:02.278 --> 17:04.540
to women thinking
they should have opinions,

17:04.611 --> 17:07.773
or jobs, or control
over their own bodies.

17:07.842 --> 17:09.374
On the other hand,

17:09.440 --> 17:11.205
all those women would worship me.

17:11.272 --> 17:12.605
On the other hand,

17:12.672 --> 17:14.867
I hate the Jews.

17:14.938 --> 17:17.602
Hmm, not sure what
that has to do with anything.

17:17.669 --> 17:19.434
Miss Bellacourt?

17:19.502 --> 17:20.867
We're waiting.

17:20.935 --> 17:23.633
Why should we allow women's suffrage?

17:23.699 --> 17:24.795
Oh.

17:24.865 --> 17:25.963
Um.

17:27.364 --> 17:29.294
<i>[INSPIRATIONAL PIANO MUSIC]</i>

17:29.363 --> 17:31.460
Because you know they're going
to get the vote eventually,

17:31.527 --> 17:33.293
and if you help make that happen,

17:33.361 --> 17:35.125
they'll vote for you and
keep you in office for life,

17:35.192 --> 17:37.622
but if you try to stop it,
they'll vote against you,

17:37.691 --> 17:39.953
and your worst fear will come true.

17:40.024 --> 17:41.954
You'll lose your power.

17:42.022 --> 17:43.953
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:44.021 --> 17:47.018
But won't you all just want
to vote for other women?

17:47.085 --> 17:49.615
Oh, uh, women hate each other.

17:49.684 --> 17:52.214
Well, you've made some
compelling points here today,

17:52.284 --> 17:54.982
and I think a lady vote
makes a lot of sense.

17:57.415 --> 18:01.177
Stop!

18:01.246 --> 18:03.009
I must speak!

18:03.076 --> 18:05.006
Like a Lazarus from the grave,

18:05.076 --> 18:07.707
I am back, you pieces of shit.

18:07.775 --> 18:09.039
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:09.108 --> 18:10.873
Hortense! You're alive?

18:10.938 --> 18:12.035
[CROWD GASPING]

18:12.104 --> 18:13.368
You look so different.

18:13.438 --> 18:14.534
Of course I look different.

18:14.603 --> 18:15.867
I've been in a car accident!

18:15.936 --> 18:17.301
That changes a woman!

18:17.369 --> 18:18.967
Do not listen to these fools,

18:19.035 --> 18:20.632
they know not what they say.

18:20.700 --> 18:23.464
The reason to allow the vote for women

18:23.532 --> 18:25.696
is because they are equal to men!

18:25.765 --> 18:27.130
No, they're not.

18:27.198 --> 18:29.861
Down with the patriarchy!

18:29.929 --> 18:31.125
You idiot!

18:31.195 --> 18:32.760
[SHRILL SCREAMING]

18:32.826 --> 18:35.890
